message.content:
cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the design of a cognitive beamforming algorithm based on the feedback from the primary user receiver. Information theory plays a crucial role in the design of such algorithms, and hence this category is the most likely.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the design of a cognitive radio network, which involves the study of networking and internet architecture. Hence, this category is also likely.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new paradigm for designing cognitive beamforming algorithms, which involves the control of the interference power at the primary user receiver. Hence, this category is also likely.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the enhancement of the secondary user link performance, which is related to multimedia applications. Hence, this category is also likely.
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with the efficient spectrum sharing between primary and secondary users, which involves the study of security and cryptography. Hence, this category is also likely.
